How the Clock Works

The clock is drawn using QPainter.

The painter is moved to the center of the widget and then scaled based on the window size.
This keeps the clock centered and prevents clipping when resizing.

A QTimer updates the widget regularly so the clock stays in sync with time.



Angle Math Explanation

Qt uses degrees for rotation and rotates clockwise.

Hour Hand

One hour = 30 degrees (360 / 12)
Minutes and seconds slightly move the hour hand forward
angle = hours * 30 + minutes * 0.5 + seconds * (0.5 / 60)

Minute Hand

One minute = 6 degrees (360 / 60)
Seconds slightly move the minute hand
angle = minutes * 6 + seconds * 0.1

Second Hand

One second = 6 degrees
Milliseconds are added for smooth motion
angle = 6 * (seconds + milliseconds / 1000)

